          "tempoGroove": "Ballads 60–76 BPM with heavy swung sixteenth-notes (the fast notes lean long-short instead of even); hip-hop-soul mid-tempos high-80s to mid-100s over a boom-bap backbeat (the snare cracking on beats 2 and 4 — classic head-nod hip-hop drums); new-jack-swing uptempos (the late-80s style that put hip-hop drums under R&B songs) roughly 104–116 with a hard bounce. Word density low-to-moderate in verses; choruses are short and endlessly repeatable.",
