          "oneLine": "The hard Fania-era sound of the barrio — aggressive brass, social weight, and a sonero who testifies over a driving montuno.",
          "tempoGroove": "~90-100 BPM counted on the quarter note (felt in cut-time, in 2 — the danced pulse is the slow half, not a fast one) locked to a 2-3 or 3-2 son clave — the hidden pulse every line must respect. Word density moderate and percussive: tight on-the-beat phrases short enough for a brass mambo to punch between them, never wall-to-wall.",
